column2:
The node No. (MAC ID) value is out of range.
The mode switch value is out of range.
column3:
Set the node No. within the range of 0 to 63.
Set the mode switch to any other than D to F.

column2: The node No. (MAC ID) is duplicated on the network.
column3: Set a unique node No.

column2: Power is not supplied to the network.
column3: Supply power to the network (DC24V).

column2: Other modules cannot be identified on the network.
column3: Connect other modules to the network.

column2: The node No. switches or mode switch has been changed during operation.
column3: Restore the setting of the node No. switches or mode switch.

column2: Zero (0) is set for both the input and output points of a slave node.
column3: Set the input and output points according to the slave node specifications.

column2: The low byte of the slave node No. in the buffer memory is out of range.
column3: Set it within the range of 0 to 63.

column2: The high byte of the slave node No. in the buffer memory is out of range.
column3: Set it within the range of 01H to 04H, or to 80H.

column2: The connection type in the buffer memory is out of range.
The same node No. has already been set for a slave node in the buffer memory.
column3: Set unique node numbers for all nodes.

column2: No slave node has been set.
column3: Set at least one slave node.

column2: The total input data length of all slave nodes is too long.
column3: Reduce it to 512 bytes or less.

column2: The total output data length of all slave nodes is too long.
column3: Reduce it to 512 bytes or less.

column2: The parameter value for the watchdog timeout action is invalid.
The expected packet rate value in the buffer memory is smaller than the production inhibit time value.
column3: Change the setting so that the expected packet rate value is greater than or equal to the production inhibit time value.

column2:
Flash ROM checksum error
(Parameters for Master Function area)
column3:
Save the parameters again.
Do not turn OFF the power or reset while saving the parameters.

column2:
Flash ROM checksum error
(Parameters for Slave Function area)
column3:
Save the parameters again.
Do not turn OFF the power or reset while saving the parameters.

column2:
Flash ROM checksum error
(Auto Communication Start Setting area)
column3:
Save the parameters again.
Do not turn OFF the power or reset while saving the parameters.

column2: Flash ROM all clear error
column3:
Clear all parameters again.
Do not turn OFF the power or reset while clearing the parameters.

column2: The number of input points per slave node exceeds 256 bytes.
column3: Correct the number of input points per slave node to 256 bytes or less.

column2: The number of output points per slave node exceeds 256 bytes.
column3: Correct the number of output points per slave node to 256 bytes or less.

column2: The production inhibit time value was set to 0 ms (set value 1) in cyclic.
column3: Set the production inhibit time value to a value other than 0 ms.

column2: All slave nodes are set as reserved nodes by parameters.
column3: Set the parameters according to the slave nodes connected to the network.

column2: Although the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the master function is set to be enabled, DNTMRD was not executed during execution of three sequence scans.
column3:
Correct the sequence program so that DNTMRD may be executed in every scan.
When not using the dedicated instruction, set the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the master function to be disabled, and turn on I/O communication request (Y11).

column2: Although the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the master function is set to be enabled, DNTMWR was not executed during execution of three sequence scans.
column3:
Correct the sequence program so that DNTMWR may be executed in every scan.
When not using the dedicated instruction, set the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the master function to be disabled, and turn on I/O communication request (Y11).

column2: Although the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the slave function is set to be enabled, DNTSRD was not executed during execution of three sequence scans.
column3:
Correct the sequence program so that DNTSRD may be executed in every scan.
When not using the dedicated instruction, set the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the slave function to be disabled, and turn on I/O communication request (Y11).

column2: Although the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the slave function is set to be enabled, DNTSWR was not executed during execution of three sequence scans.
column3:
Correct the sequence program so that DNTSWR may be executed in every scan.
When not using the dedicated instruction, set the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the slave function to be disabled, and turn on I/O communication request (Y11).

column2: When using the master function, the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the slave function was set to be enabled, and I/O communications were started.
column3: Set the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the slave function to be disabled, and turn on I/O communication request (Y11).

column2: When using the slave function, the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the master function was set to be enabled, and I/O communications were started.
column3: Set the data separation-inhibiting dedicated instruction setting for the master function to be disabled, and turn on I/O communication request (Y11).

column2: The number of slave function receive bytes is out of range.
column3: Set it within the range of 0 to 128 bytes.

column2: The number of slave function transmit bytes is out of range.
column3: Set it within the range of 0 to 128 bytes.

column2:
Both of the slave function transmit and receive bytes are set 
to 0.
column3: Set either of the transmit or receive bytes to any other than 0.

column2: When using both the master and slave functions, the number of I/O points is set to 0 for both of them.
column3:
Set I/O points of slave nodes in Parameters for Master Function.
Set transmit/receive bytes in Parameters for Slave Function.
(Either of master or slave function values must be set.)
